{
  "texts": [
    "The former is used as a database while the latter one is used as query.",
    "The two sequences are for evaluating the performance for large-scale long-term place recognition.",
    "HPointLoc (Yudin et al. 2023): HPointLoc is a point cloud-based indoor place recognition dataset with synthetic RGB-D images.",
    "It is based on the popular Habitat (Savva et al. 2019) simulator from 49 photorealistic indoor scenes from the Matterport3D (Chang et al. 2017) dataset and contains 76,000 frames.",
    "The HPointLoc dataset is split into two parts: the validation HPointLoc-Val, which contains only one scene, and the complete HPointLoc-All dataset, containing all 49 scenes, including HPointLoc-Val."
  ]
}